results.description: The hike to Mt Fitzroy in Argentina is pleasant and not difficult for the most part, just long. Until you get to the final half an hour, which is a gruelling 30minute uphill battle at 45degrees to reach the base of the mountain. On the day we were hiking, there was cloud cover and extreme winds throwing ice into our faces as we reached the top. Mt Fitzroy is actually to the left of this side peak, but it was covered in clouds and we never saw it in the end. This calm, minimal photo is a complete juxtaposition to the situation it was photographed in.
